column5: Boats ready and hut goes in the nest.
Plan on doing that this weekend myself. At least get the bearings done on the trailer, hopefully more.  Looking forward to a longer boating season then the last one.
AMEN, and Hallelujah!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  Those spring weekends last year were a disaster as far as getting out with my 14'er!
See you on the water Dave. Had my boat out for two weeks now.
See you out there Steve, I'm still thinking about your trip to Nipigon, your trip blew my mind. Are you doing the 1 day Cat derby in April at Steve's?
ANOTHER Great Farm Report.......  My fishing machine is due out on the 15th......
I just called the "Farmer" to see if he was waxing the hull, wimp said it was too cold.....
For some reason,I dont believe you.
I would love to but I have charter that day on the grand. I will let you know when the cats start to bite.I got two more guys to go to Nipigon this year.
I'm going to work on a couple guys to do the Nipigon thing Thanks Steve
